metadata.name: HashCrafts #24
metadata.description:
HashCrafts is a series of digital spacecraft and alien pilots flying through space on Tezos. Wanted to create a generative token that had a unique look and combine generative selection with handmade drawings.

There are 25 different traits and 6 different attributes as well as an infinite amount of color combinations.

Seven different alien pilots. The rarest being "The Twins".

Four different domes. The rarest being "Ears".

Four different ships. Two rarest ships, one being "F1SH".

Four different hulls. The rarest being a laser weapon.

Finally you have a 2% chance of minting a grayscale HashCraft.

Had tons of fun with this experimental handdrawn generative project and I hope people enjoy collecting their own happy alien armada.

metadata.name: Sketch E #149
metadata.description:
Sketch is an open-ended series. Works evolve as I code a generative project, sometimes drastically. Intermediate works usually don't see the light of day - they get archived and forgotten. This series is snapshots of different forms along the way - each standing alone, but also part of a larger meandering work flow. The word Sketch implies incompleteness. This project may end up being two works, or it could evolve for years. Part of the joy of generative art is never knowing what's around the corner. I have no set schedule. There may be multiple Sketches released a week, or it could be weeks or months between drops. I have no idea where Sketch is heading and there is no guarantee of cohesiveness from Sketch to Sketch. Color palettes and forms will change as new ideas are explored.

Sketch E. Rebuilding after the disruption of Sketch D. Color palettes from A-D remain and more palettes are introduced based on Werner's Nomenclature of Colors, first published in 1814, which served as a classification guide for natural colors before photography became commonplace and used by Charles Darwin during voyages on the HMS Beagle. Grid size, padding, and colors vary.

Press the spacebar to see the framework and press the left/right arrow keys to construct and deconstruct.

metadata.name: *Re^iTheta #50
metadata.description:
"*Re^iTheta" (pronounced "Starry Eye Theta‚Äù) generates patterns with an Iterated Function System parameterized by a single complex number given in polar form as Z =Re^(iTheta), where the two parameters R and Theta are randomly chosen according to the fxhash. The pattern is constructed by joining lines between the sequence of points in the plane defined by taking the number Z and consecutively multiplying it by itself 500 times. The resulting shape is then colored with two randomly chosen complementary colors such that adjacent regions differ in color. The points are then modulated for dynamic effect.

R describes a "contraction" factor in the range: 0.96 < R < 0.98

Theta describes a relative "angle" in the range (radians): 0.785 < Theta < 2.984

Parameter values are divided into three levels according to their magnitude, where "low" and "mid" levels are equally likely and "high" levels occur with a 20% chance.

**click/touch** the Canvas to dynamically generate the pattern through the sequence of points.
